The Seoul, Korea 1988 Summer Olympics closed on Sunday.  9,633 athletes from 160 
nations competed in 34 venues.  At least 1 billion people watched via a 115-nation 
worldwide TV hookup.  It was the first meeting between the Soviet Union and the United 
States since 1976.  The Soviets captured the most medals, the U.S. third most.  Among 
the U.S. highlights were championships won by Greg Louganis, Florence Griffith Joyner, 
Jackie Joyner-Kersee and Matt Biondi.  A big Olympic negative was the stripping of the 
gold medal from Canadian sprinter Ben Johnson because of drug use.  He flew home in 
disgrace.</SUM>          

<SUM
DOCSET="d087"
TYPE="PERDOC"
