Dave Johnson of the United States clinched the decathlon gold medal in the final event at 
the World University Games on Sunday.  Johnson trailed Mikhail Medved of the Soviet 
Union by 11 points before the 1,500-meter race, the final event of the two-day 
competition.  In some other events:  Julius Kariuki of Kenya won the men's 10,000-meter 
race; Romania won four golds in rowing and two in track and field; Reggie Davis won 
the gold for the U.S. in the 400-meter hurdles; Ana Quirot of Cuba won the women's 
400-meter race and Jaime Jefferson of Cuba won the men's long jump.</SUM> 

