Milan Bakes of Czechoslovakia, 27, set a world record in the kneeling portion of the 
three-position rifle competition on Friday at the 1990 World Cup USA Olympic-style 
shooting tournament.  By scoring 396 of a possible 400 points, it helped earn him a gold 
medal, which he did by scoring 1,275.9 out of a possible 1,309 for all three positions - 
kneeling, standing and prone.  Francoise Decharne of France won the women's air rifle 
competition, Young Jin of South Korea was second and Deena Wigger of the U.S. third.  
Jasna Sekaric of Yugoslavia won her second gold in the women's air pistol.</SUM>  

