In tonight's Barcelona Olympics, the four relay finals will dominate the athletics.  The 
relays, more than other events, traditionally go to affluent countries that choose to lavish 
resources on athletes.  The U.S. has won the most relay medals followed by Britain, the 
former Soviet Union, former West and East Germany, then France and Canada.  Also 
tonight, Carl Lewis will pursue his eight Olympic gold.  While winning gold brings 
excitement or relief to others, Lewis just seems unsurprised.  Noureddine Morcelli of 
Algeria should win the men's 1,500-meters.  He is one of five Africans striving to 
increase their continent's current tally of three medals.</SUM>
